ing to package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n2. **Cook the beef**: In a large pan, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the beef slices and cook until browned. Remove from pan and set aside.\n3. **Sauté the vegetables**: In the same pan, add butter and sauté the onions until translucent. Add garlic and mushrooms and cook until the mushrooms are tender.\n4. **Make the sauce**: Add beef broth and mustard to the pan. Stir well and bring to a simmer.\n5. **Combine and serve**: Return the beef to the pan and stir in sour cream. Cook until heated through. Serve over egg noodles.\n\n## Tips\n- You can substitute Greek yogurt for sour cream for a lighter version.\n- Add a splash of white wine to the sauce for extra flavor.\n- Garnish with fresh parsley or dill before serving.','2024-08-03 22:12:05.215383','2024-08-05 22:01:35.653324',1,0,4,0,62,1,1,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1370,16),(46,'Classic Caesar Salad','Classic Caesar Salad\nIngredients\nRomaine Lettuce: 1 head, chopped\nCroutons: 1 cup\nParmesan Cheese: 1','# Classic Caesar Salad\n\n![Classic Caesar Salad](https://www.grocery.coop/sites/default/files/NCG_Dennis_Becker_Classic_Caesar_Salad_715_x_477.jpg)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Romaine Lettuce: 1 head, chopped\n- Croutons: 1 cup\n- Parmesan Cheese: 1/2 cup, grated\n- Caesar Dressing: 1/2 cup\n- Lemon Wedges: for serving\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Prepare the lettuce**: Wash and chop the romaine lettuce. Place in a large salad bowl.\n2. **Add croutons and cheese**: Sprinkle croutons and grated Parmesan cheese over the lettuce.\n3. **Dress the salad**: Drizzle Caesar dressing over the salad and toss to combine.\n4. **Serve**: Serve with lemon wedges on the side.\n\n## Tips\n- For homemade croutons, toast bread cubes with olive oil and garlic in the oven until golden brown.\n- Add grilled chicken or shrimp for a more substantial meal.\n- Use freshly grated Parmesan for the best flavor.','2024-08-03 22:13:21.811418','2024-08-05 22:01:35.650758',1,0,4,0,83,1,1,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,866,34),(47,'Thai Green Curry','Thai Green Curry\nIngredients\nChicken Breast: 500g, sliced\nGreen Curry Paste: 2 tbsp\nCoconut Milk: 40','# Thai Green Curry\n\n![Thai Green Curry](https://piquantpost.com/cdn/shop/articles/GJ16a1y2HDD3gYjmojg2t_1000x.jpg?v=1646021297)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Chicken Breast: 500g, sliced\n- Green Curry Paste: 2 tbsp\n- Coconut Milk: 400ml\n- Green Beans: 200g, trimmed\n- Bamboo Shoots: 1 can, drained\n- Thai Basil: a handful\n- Fish Sauce: 2 tbsp\n- Brown Sugar: 1 tbsp\n- Lime Leaves: 2, torn\n- Jasmine Rice: for serving\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook the chicken**: In a large pan, heat some oil over medium-high heat. Add the green curry paste and fry for a few seconds until fragrant. Add the chicken slices and cook until browned.\n2. **Add the coconut milk**: Pour in the coconut milk and bring to a simmer.\n3. **Add vegetables**: Add the green beans, bamboo shoots, fish sauce, brown sugar, and lime leaves. Cook until the vegetables are tender.\n4. **Finish and serve**: Stir in Thai basil leaves just before serving. Serve hot with jasmine rice.\n\n## Tips\n- Adjust the amount of curry paste based on your spice preference.\n- Substitute chicken with tofu for a vegetarian version.\n- Garnish with fresh cilantro and a squeeze of lime for added flavor.','2024-08-03 22:14:47.729256','2024-08-05 22:01:35.648838',1,0,5,0,0,0,1,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1133,25),(48,'Apple Pie','Apple Pie\nIngredients\nApples: 6, peeled and sliced\nSugar: 1 cup\nCinnamon: 1 tsp\nNutmeg: 1/2 tsp\nLemo','# Apple Pie\n\n![Apple Pie](https://mojo.generalmills.com/api/public/content/RF7rt2cyH0GGi0OySrmZnQ_webp_base.webp?v=ce55fe91&t=e724eca7b3c24a8aaa6e089ed9e611fd)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Apples: 6, peeled and sliced\n- Sugar: 1 cup\n- Cinnamon: 1 tsp\n- Nutmeg: 1/2 tsp\n- Lemon Juice: 2 tbsp\n- Pie Crust: 2, ready-made\n- Butter: 2 tbsp, cubed\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Prepare the filling**: In a large bowl, combine the apple slices, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and lemon juice. Mix well.\n2. **Assemble the pie**: Place one pie crust in a pie dish. Fill with the apple mixture and dot with butter cubes. Cover with the second pie crust, sealing the edges and cutting slits for steam.\n3. **Bake the pie**: Preheat the oven to 200°C (400°F). Bake the pie for 45-50 minutes, until the crust is golden brown.\n4. **Serve**: Let the pie cool before serving. Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.\n\n## Tips\n- Use a mix of sweet and tart apples for a balanced flavor.\n- Brush the top crust with an egg wash for a shiny finish.\n- Add a tablespoon of flour to the filling to thicken the juices.','2024-08-03 22:16:28.537691','2024-08-05 22:01:35.647347',1,0,3,0,90,1,1,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1074,3),(49,'Vegetarian Chili','Vegetarian Chili\nIngredients\nKidney Beans: 2 cans, drained\nBlack Beans: 2 cans, drained\nCorn: 1 can,','# Vegetarian Chili\n\n![Vegetarian Chili](data:image/jpeg;base64,)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Kidney Beans: 2 cans, drained\n- Black Beans: 2 cans, drained\n- Corn: 1 can, drained\n- Bell Peppers: 2, diced\n- Onion: 1, chopped\n- Garlic: 2 cloves, minced\n- Tomatoes: 2 cans, diced\n- Tomato Paste: 2 tbsp\n- Chili Powder: 2 tbsp\n- Cumin: 1 tbsp\n- Olive Oil: 2 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n- Cilantro: for garnish\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Sauté the vegetables**: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add the onions and bell peppers, and sauté until softened. Add the garlic and cook for another minute.\n2. **Add the beans and corn**: Stir in the kidney beans, black beans, and corn.\n3. **Add tomatoes and spices**: Add the diced tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder, and cumin. Stir well and bring to a simmer.\n4. **Cook the chili**: Reduce heat and let the chili simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n5. **Serve**: Season with salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with cilantro before serving.\n\n## Tips\n- Serve with shredded cheese, sour cream, and avocado slices for added flavor.\n- Make a large batch and freeze leftovers for easy meals.\n- Add a chopped jalapeño for extra heat.','2024-08-03 22:17:57.262524','2024-08-05 22:01:35.642180',1,0,4,0,6,0,1,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,22853,27),(50,'The Greek Taverna','The Greek Taverna\nLocation\n789 Mediterranean Lane, City\nDescription\nThe Greek Taverna offers an auth','# The Greek Taverna\n\n![The Greek Taverna](https://www.greekboston.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Taverna.jpg)\n\n## Location\n789 Mediterranean Lane, City\n\n## Description\nThe Greek Taverna offers an authentic Greek dining experience with a menu full of traditional dishes. The ambiance is warm and welcoming, perfect for family gatherings.\n\n## Must-Try Dishes\n- Moussaka\n- Gyro Plate\n- Baklava\n\n## Review\nThe Greek Taverna is a wonderful place to enjoy traditional Greek cuisine. The Moussaka is rich and flavorful, the Gyro Plate is packed with deliciously seasoned meat, and the Baklava is perfectly sweet and flaky.\n\n## Additional Information\nThe Greek Taverna also offers a variety of Greek wines and ouzo. The staff is friendly and the service is prompt. It\'s an ideal spot for a relaxed dinner or a celebration. Reservations are recommended during weekends.\n\n## Contact\n- Phone: (678) 901-2345\n- Website: www.thegreektaverna.com','2024-08-03 22:24:09.034684','2024-08-05 22:01:35.640506',1,0,2,0,237,1,2,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,931,3),(51,'Indian Delight','Indian Delight\nLocation\n456 Spice Road, City\nDescription\nIndian Delight serves a variety of flavorfu','# Indian Delight\n\n![Indian Delight](https://tajrestaurant.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/pexels-chan-walrus-958545.jpg)\n\n## Location\n456 Spice Road, City\n\n## Description\nIndian Delight serves a variety of flavorful Indian dishes in a vibrant setting. The restaurant is known for its rich curries and freshly baked naan.\n\n## Must-Try Dishes\n- Butter Chicken\n- Paneer Tikka\n- Mango Lassi\n\n## Review\nIndian De