ch Brasserie\n\n## Location\n321 Paris Boulevard, City\n\n## Description\nThe French Brasserie offers a fine dining experience with a menu full of classic French dishes. The restaurant has a sophisticated ambiance, perfect for special occasions.\n\n## Must-Try Dishes\n- Coq au Vin\n- Duck Confit\n- Crème Brûlée\n\n## Review\nThe French Brasserie is a fantastic place to experience authentic French cuisine. The Coq au Vin is rich and savory, the Duck Confit is tender and flavorful, and the Crème Brûlée is the perfect ending to a delightful meal.\n\n## Additional Information\nThe French Brasserie also offers an extensive wine list with selections from France and beyond. The service is impeccable, and the atmosphere is elegant. It\'s a great spot for a romantic dinner or a celebration. Reservations are highly recommended.\n\n## Contact\n- Phone: (234) 567-8901\n- Website: www.thefrenchbrasserie.com\n\n\n![The French Brasserie](https://bdc2020.o0bc.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Brasserie-plates-6091a21d3914b-768x432.jpg)','2024-08-03 22:29:10.225718','2024-08-05 22:01:35.636180',1,0,2,0,226,1,2,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1017,25),(54,'Mexican Fiesta','Mexican Fiesta\nLocation\n456 Fiesta Avenue, City\nDescription\nMexican Fiesta offers a vibrant dining e','# Mexican Fiesta\n\n## Location\n456 Fiesta Avenue, City\n\n## Description\nMexican Fiesta offers a vibrant dining experience with a menu full of traditional Mexican dishes. The restaurant is known for its lively atmosphere and delicious margaritas.\n\n## Must-Try Dishes\n- Enchiladas\n- Tacos al Pastor\n- Churros\n\n## Review\nMexican Fiesta is a fun and lively place to enjoy authentic Mexican food. The Enchiladas are cheesy and flavorful, the Tacos al Pastor are perfectly seasoned, and the Churros are crispy and sweet.\n\n## Additional Information\nThe restaurant has a colorful and festive decor, making it a great spot for celebrations. The staff is friendly and the service is quick. They also offer catering services for parties and events.\n\n## Contact\n- Phone: (345) 678-9012\n- Website: www.mexicanfiesta.com\n\n![Mexican Fiesta](https://veggiefestchicago.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Mexican-Fiesta-Salad-Wb.jpg)','2024-08-03 22:30:53.080279','2024-08-05 22:01:35.633908',1,0,2,0,112,1,2,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,909,15),(55,'Pesto Pasta','Pesto Pasta\nIngredients\nPasta: 200g\nPesto Sauce: 1/2 cup\nCherry Tomatoes: 1 cup, halved\nParmesan Che','# Pesto Pasta\n\n![Pesto Pasta](https://www.forksoverknives.com/uploads/One-Pot-Pesto-Pasta-wordpress.jpg?auto=webp)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Pasta: 200g\n- Pesto Sauce: 1/2 cup\n- Cherry Tomatoes: 1 cup, halved\n- Parmesan Cheese: 1/4 cup, grated\n- Olive Oil: 1 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook the pasta**: Bring a pot of salted water to a boil and cook the pasta according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n2. **Prepare the sauce**: In a large bowl, toss the cooked pasta with pesto sauce, cherry tomatoes, and olive oil.\n3. **Serve**: Season with salt and pepper to taste. Top with grated Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.\n\n## Tips\n- Use fresh basil pesto for the best flavor.\n- Add a handful of baby spinach or arugula for extra greens.\n- Serve with garlic bread for a complete meal.\n\n## Additional Information\nPesto pasta is a versatile dish that can be enjoyed hot or cold, making it perfect for quick lunches or easy dinners. The bright green pesto sauce pairs wonderfully with the sweetness of cherry tomatoes and the nutty flavor of Parmesan cheese. For a heartier meal, consider adding grilled chicken or shrimp.','2024-08-03 22:34:41.972434','2024-08-05 22:01:35.632104',1,0,2,0,102,1,3,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1152,4),(56,'Egg Fried Rice','Egg Fried Rice\nIngredients\nCooked Rice: 2 cups, chilled\nEggs: 2, beaten\nGreen Peas: 1/2 cup\nCarrots:','# Egg Fried Rice\n\n![Egg Fried Rice](https://www.masala.tv/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/EGG-FRIED-RICEr.jpg)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Cooked Rice: 2 cups, chilled\n- Eggs: 2, beaten\n- Green Peas: 1/2 cup\n- Carrots: 1/2 cup, diced\n- Green Onions: 2, sliced\n- Soy Sauce: 2 tbsp\n- Sesame Oil: 1 tsp\n- Vegetable Oil: 2 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook the vegetables**: Heat vegetable oil in a large pan or wok over medium-high heat. Add the carrots and cook until tender. Add the peas and cook for another minute.\n2. **Add the eggs**: Push the vegetables to the side and pour the beaten eggs into the pan. Scramble until fully cooked.\n3. **Fry the rice**: Add the cooked rice to the pan and stir to combine with the vegetables and eggs. Cook until heated through.\n4. **Season and serve**: Stir in soy sauce and sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot.\n\n## Tips\n- Use day-old rice for the best texture.\n- Add cooked chicken, shrimp, or tofu for added protein.\n- Garnish with extra green onions and sesame seeds for a finishing touch.\n\n## Additional Information\nEgg fried rice is a great way to use up leftover rice and vegetables. It\'s a quick and easy meal that can be customized with your favorite ingredients. For a spicy kick, add a splash of hot sauce or a sprinkle of red pepper flakes. This dish is perfect for a weeknight dinner or a simple lunch.','2024-08-03 22:36:11.361328','2024-08-05 22:01:35.630542',1,0,2,0,120,1,3,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1384,31),(57,'Tomato Basil Soup','Tomato Basil Soup\nIngredients\nTomatoes: 6, chopped\nOnion: 1, chopped\nGarlic: 2 cloves, minced\nVegeta','# Tomato Basil Soup\n\n![Tomato Basil Soup](https://hips.hearstapps.com/del.h-cdn.co/assets/15/44/1600x900/hd-aspect-1446063831-weeknight-din-tomato-soup.jpg?resize=1200:*)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Tomatoes: 6, chopped\n- Onion: 1, chopped\n- Garlic: 2 cloves, minced\n- Vegetable Broth: 4 cups\n- Fresh Basil: a handful, chopped\n- Olive Oil: 2 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n- Cream: 1/2 cup (optional)\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook the vegetables**: Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onions and garlic, and cook until softened. Add the tomatoes and cook for another 5 minutes.\n2. **Add the broth**: Pour in the vegetable broth and bring to a simmer. Cook for 20 minutes.\n3. **Blend the soup**: Use an immersion blender to blend the soup until smooth. Alternatively, transfer the soup to a blender and blend in batches.\n4. **Season and serve**: Stir in the chopped basil and season with salt and pepper to taste. Add cream if using. Serve hot.\n\n## Tips\n- For a richer flavor, roast the tomatoes and garlic before adding them to the soup.\n- Serve with crusty bread or grilled cheese sandwiches.\n- Garnish with extra basil leaves and a drizzle of olive oil.\n\n## Additional Information\nTomato basil soup is a comforting classic that is perfect for any time of the year. The fresh basil adds a wonderful aroma and flavor to the soup. This recipe can be made in advance and stored in the refrigerator for up to a week or frozen for up to three months. Pair it with a salad or sandwich for a complete meal.','2024-08-03 22:46:14.654324','2024-08-05 22:01:35.628920',1,0,4,0,121,1,3,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1506,20),(58,'Chicken Quesadillas','Chicken Quesadillas\nIngredients\nChicken Breast: 2, cooked and shredded\nTortillas: 4\nCheddar Cheese: ','# Chicken Quesadillas\n\n![Chicken Quesadillas](https://img.sndimg.com/food/image/upload/f_auto,c_thumb,q_55,w_860,ar_3:2/v1/img/recipes/39/78/Ve6XwMvToypkQvkIyESC_0S9A1605.jpg)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Chicken Breast: 2, cooked and shredded\n- Tortillas: 4\n- Cheddar Cheese: 2 cups, shredded\n- Bell Peppers: 1, sliced\n- Onion: 1, sliced\n- Olive Oil: 1 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n- Salsa and Sour Cream: for serving\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook the vegetables**: Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add the bell peppers and onion, and cook until tender. Season with salt and pepper.\n2. **Assemble the quesadillas**: Place a tortilla in a large skillet over medium heat. Sprinkle half with cheese, then add shredded chicken and cooked vegetables. Top with more cheese and fold the tortilla in half.\n3. **Cook the quesadillas**: Cook until the bottom is golden brown, then flip and cook the other side until golden and the cheese is melted.\n4. **Serve**: Cut into wedges and serve with salsa and sour cream.\n\n## Tips\n- Add black beans or corn for extra flavor and texture.\n- Use a combination of cheeses like Monterey Jack and mozzarella.\n- Serve with guacamole and hot sauce for added zest.\n\n## Additional Information\nChicken quesadillas are a versatile and delicious meal that can be customized with your favorite fillings. They are perfect for a quick lunch or dinner and can be served with a variety of sides such as rice, beans, or a salad. This recipe can also be made vegetarian by using beans and vegetables instead of chicken.','2024-08-03 22:48:40.619647','2024-08-05 22:01:35.627616',1,0,2,0,108,1,3,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1530,41),(59,'Spinach and Feta Stuffed Chicken','Spinach and Feta Stuffed Chicken\nIngredients\nChicken Breasts: 4, boneless and skinless\nFresh Spinach','# Spinach and Feta Stuffed Chicken\n\n## Ingredients\n- Chicken Breasts: 4, boneless and skinless\n- Fresh Spinach: 2 cups, chopped\n- Feta Cheese: 1 cup, crumbled\n- Garlic: 2 cloves, minced\n- Olive Oil: 2 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Prepare the filling**: In a pan, heat 1 tbsp olive oil over medium heat. Add garlic and sauté until fragrant. Add spinach and cook until wilted. Remove from heat and mix with crumbled feta cheese.\n2. **Stuff the chicken**: Cut a pocket into each chicken breast and stuff with the spinach and feta mixture. Secure with toothpicks if needed.\n3. **Cook the chicken**: Heat the remaining olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add the stuffed chicken breasts and cook until golden brown on both sides and cooked through.\n4. **Serve**: Serve hot with your favorite side dishes.\n\n## Tips\n- Use a meat thermometer to ensure the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 75°C (165°F).\n- Serve with a side of roasted vegetables or a fresh salad.\n- Add sun-dried tomatoes or olives to the filling for extra flavor.\n\n## Additional Information\nStuffed chicken breasts are an elegant yet easy dish that can be prepared quickly. The combination of spinach and feta provides a delicious and nutritious filling that keeps the chicken moist and flavorful. This dish is perfect for weeknight dinners or special occasions.\n\n![Spinach and Feta Stuffed Chicken](https://basilandbubbly.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/spinachstuffedchickenabove.jpg)','2024-08-03 22:50:13.226627','2024-08-05 22:01:35.626005',1,0,3,0,124,1,3,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1487,34),(60,'Quinoa Stuffed Peppers','Quinoa Stuffed Peppers\nIngredients\nBell Peppers: 4, halved and seeded\nQuinoa: 1 cup, cooked\nBlack Be','# Quinoa Stuffed Peppers\n\n![Quinoa Stuffed Peppers](https://www.365daysofbakingandmore.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Quinoa-BlackBean-Turkey-Stuffed-Peppers-1.jpg)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Bell Peppers: 4, halved and seeded\n- Quinoa: 1 cup, cooked\n- Black Beans: 1 can, drained and rinsed\n- Corn: 1 cup\n- Cherry Tomatoes: 1 cup, halved\n- Red Onion: 1/2, diced\n- Cilantro: a handful, chopped\n- Lime Juice: 2 tbsp\n- Olive Oil: 1 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat the oven**: Preheat your oven to 190°C (375°F).\n2. **Prepare the filling**: In a large bowl, combine cooked quinoa, black beans, corn, cherry tomatoes, red onion, cilantro, lime juice, olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n3. **Stuff the peppers**: Place bell pepper halves in a baking dish and fill with the quinoa mixture.\n4. **Bake**: Cover with foil and bake for 25-30 minutes until the peppers are tender.\n5. **Serve**: Serve hot, optionally garnished with extra cilantro and a squeeze of lime juice.\n\n## Tips\n- Add shredded cheese on top before baking for a cheesy version.\n- Use different colored bell peppers for a vibrant presentation.\n- Serve with a side of avocado slices or guacamole.\n\n## Additional Information\nQuinoa stuffed peppers are a nutritious and satisfying meal that is perfect for a healthy dinner. The combination of quinoa, beans, and vegetables provides a good balance of protein, fiber, and vitamins. This dish is also versatile and can be customized with your favorite ingredients.','2024-08-03 22:51:52.710877','2024-08-05 22:01:35.624275',1,0,2,0,163,1,5,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1481,25),(61,'Grilled Salmon with Avocado Salsa','Grilled Salmon with Avocado Salsa\nIngredients\nSalmon Fillets: 4\nOlive Oil: 2 tbsp\nSalt & Pepper to t','# Grilled Salmon with Avocado Salsa\n\n![Grilled Salmon with Avocado Salsa](https://i.ytimg.com/vi/oY3S6acQ9lE/maxresdefault.jpg)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Salmon Fillets: 4\n- Olive Oil: 2 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n- Avocado: 1, diced\n- Tomato: 1, diced\n- Red Onion: 1/4, diced\n- Cilantro: a handful, chopped\n- Lime Juice: 1 tbsp\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat the grill**: Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.\n2. **Season the salmon**: Brush the salmon fillets with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.\n3. **Grill the salmon**: Place the salmon fillets on the grill, skin-side down, and cook for 4-5 minutes per side until fully cooked.\n4. **Prepare the salsa**: In a bowl, combine diced avocado, tomato, red onion, cilantro, and lime juice. Mix gently.\n5. **Serve**: Serve the grilled salmon with a generous topping of avocado salsa.\n\n## Tips\n- For a smoky flavor, add a touch of smoked paprika to the salmon seasoning.\n- Serve with a side of quinoa or brown rice for a complete meal.\n- Garnish with lime wedges and extra cilantro for a fresh finish.\n\n## Additional Information\nGrilled salmon with avocado salsa is a light and healthy meal that is full of flavor. The creamy avocado salsa complements the grilled salmon perfectly, making it a delicious and nutritious dinner option. This dish is quick to prepare and can be enjoyed any time of the year.','2024-08-03 22:53:17.649725','2024-08-05 22:01:35.622728',1,0,3,0,155,1,5,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1357,40),(62,'Sweet Potato and Black Bean Tacos','Sweet Potato and Black Bean Tacos\nIngredients\nSweet Potatoes: 2, peeled and diced\nBlack Beans: 1 can','# Sweet Potato and Black Bean Tacos\n\n![Sweet Potato and Black Bean Tacos](https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5b47a46b30006c0de316d802-8bfc3c25.jpg)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Sweet Potatoes: 2, peeled and diced\n- Black Beans: 1 can, drained and rinsed\n- Olive Oil: 2 tbsp\n- Cumin: 1 tsp\n- Chili Powder: 1 tsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n- Corn Tortillas: 8\n- Avocado: 1, sliced\n- Fresh Cilantro: a handful, chopped\n- Lime: 1, cut into wedges\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat the oven**: Preheat your oven to 200°C (400°F).\n2. **Roast the sweet potatoes**: Toss the diced sweet potatoes with olive oil, cumin, chili powder, salt, and pepper. Spread on a baking sheet and roast for 25-30 minutes until tender.\n3. **Heat the beans**: In a small pan, heat the black beans until warmed through.\n4. **Assemble the tacos**: Warm the corn tortillas and fill with roasted sweet potatoes and black beans. Top with avocado slices and fresh cilantro.\n5. **Serve**: Serve with lime wedges on the side.\n\n## Tips\n- Add a drizzle of lime crema or yogurt sauce for extra creaminess.\n- Use flour tortillas if preferred.\n- Serve with a side of salsa or hot sauce for added flavor.\n\n## Additional Information\nSweet potato and black bean tacos are a delicious and healthy meal that is perfect for a quick and easy dinner. The combination of sweet potatoes and black beans provides a good balance of carbohydrates and protein, while the avocado adds healthy fats. These tacos are also vegetarian and gluten-free, making them suitable for a variety of dietary preferences.','2024-08-03 22:54:14.847337','2024-08-05 22:01:35.620950',1,0,2,0,226,1,5,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1576,31),(63,'Berry Smoothie Bowl','Berry Smoothie Bowl\nIngredients\nFrozen Mixed Berries: 1 cup\nBanana: 1\nGreek Yogurt: 1/2 cup\nAlmond M','# Berry Smoothie Bowl\n\n![Berry Smoothie Bowl](https://images.contentstack.io/v3/assets/blt9039451385f46c16/blt90fcbdc16065c080/635f7a11d7065f298ba9181e/SANI021_AcaiBowl_1166-HiRes.jpg?width=910&height=400&format=jpg&quality=95&crop=910%3A400)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Frozen Mixed Berries: 1 cup\n- Banana: 1\n- Greek Yogurt: 1/2 cup\n- Almond Milk: 1/4 cup\n- Granola: 1/4 cup\n- Fresh Berries: for topping\n- Chia Seeds: 1 tbsp\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Blend the ingredients**: In a blender, combine the frozen mixed berries, banana, Greek yogurt, and almond milk. Blend until smooth.\n2. **Pour into a bowl**: Pour the smoothie into a bowl.\n3. **Add toppings**: Top with granola, fresh berries, and chia seeds.\n4. **Serve**: Serve immediately.\n\n## Tips\n- Use a mix of your favorite berries for a personalized flavor.\n- Add a spoonful of nut butter for extra protein and creaminess.\n- Garnish with mint leaves or shredded coconut for a fresh twist.\n\n## Additional Information\nBerry smoothie bowls are a refreshing and nutritious breakfast or snack option. They are packed with antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals, making them a great way to start your day. The toppings can be customized to your liking, and the smoothie base can be made ahead of time and stored in the freezer for a quick and easy meal.','2024-08-03 22:55:43.673290','2024-08-05 22:01:35.619389',1,0,2,0,168,1,5,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1290,4),(64,'Lentil Soup','Lentil Soup\nIngredients\nLentils: 1 cup, rinsed\nCarrots: 2, diced\nCelery: 2 stalks, diced\nOnion: 1, c','# Lentil Soup\n\n![Lentil Soup](https://www.howtocook.recipes/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Lentil-soup-recipe-500x375.jpg)\n\n## Ingredients\n- Lentils: 1 cup, rinsed\n- Carrots: 2, diced\n- Celery: 2 stalks, diced\n- Onion: 1, chopped\n- Garlic: 2 cloves, minced\n- Vegetable Broth: 4 cups\n- Diced Tomatoes: 1 can\n- Cumin: 1 tsp\n- Turmeric: 1/2 tsp\n- Olive Oil: 2 tbsp\n- Salt & Pepper to taste\n- Fresh Parsley: for garnish\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Sauté the vegetables**: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add the onions, carrots, and celery, and cook until softened. Add the garlic and cook for another minute.\n2. **Add the lentils and spices**: Stir in the lentils, cumin, turmeric, salt, and pepper.\n3. **Add the broth and tomatoes**: Pour in the vegetable broth and diced tomatoes. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 25-30 minutes until the lentils are tender.\n4. **Serve**: Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley.\n\n## Tips\n- Add a squeeze of lemon juice before serving for a burst of freshness.\n- Serve with crusty bread or a side salad.\n- Adjust the seasoning to taste and add more spices if desired.\n\n## Additional Information\nLentil soup is a hearty and nutritious meal that is perfect for any time of the year. It is packed with protein and fiber, making it a filling and satisfying option. This recipe is also versatile and can be customized with your favorite vegetables and spices. Lentil soup is easy to make in large batches and can be frozen for future meals.','2024-08-03 22:56:59.402423','2024-08-05 22:01:35.616344',1,0,2,0,116,1,5,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,1490,37),(65,'Test Author','Test','Test','2024-08-13 14:22:47.472050','2024-08-13 14:22:47.472096',1,0,2,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,0,41),(66,'Hello','Hello','Hello','2024-08-13 14:25:08.895659','2024-08-13 14:25:08.895706',1,0,1,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Mimi','Mimi Food Blog',NULL,0,36);
